    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Blêktre 2081 is an <strong>open-world sandbox RPG</strong> set in a dystopian future uncomfortably close to our own. You play a migrant arriving in a ruthless turbo-capitalist society where humans themselves have become commodities, somewhere between Soylent Green and South Park.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Explore a fully simulated open city and decide how to survive within it. Find housing, develop your character, earn money, gain influence — or break into someone else’s apartment just to take a shit on their carpet. Every approach is part of the same systemic world.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Build your place in Blêktre by taking on countless roles: beggar, corpse-collecting worker, predatory entrepreneur, business robber, cop enforcing order on demo players, or ultimately President, empowered to rewrite the laws governing the world itself — even deciding whether the game should become free.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The persistent shared world can be played entirely solo while remaining continuously shaped by other players’ actions, allowing cooperation, rivalry, or complete independence inside the same evolving city.</p>",
